modal.heading: Wheelchair users
modal.content:
To be absolutely sure you're allocated a hotel room with wheelchair access, please call {{tel}} (choose your langauge, then select option 6) or contact us via our online webform.

We recommend against booking a hotel with wheelchair access online as we want to ensure your booking is allocated to specific rooms in one of our carefully chosen accessible hotels.

You can shortlist the hotels available on the dates you wish to travel by using the Disabled Facilities option under the Facilities filter in our hotel search.

accordionContents.title: Can I book a day trip on Snap?

children.text: No, you can't book a same day return using Snap.​

accordionContents.title: My plans have changed, what’s the Snap ticket exchange/refund policy?

children.text: Snap tickets are non-exchangeable, non-refundable, non-transferable and non-cancellable.​

accordionContents.title: I was on a train that was delayed, can I claim compensation?

children.text: Our usual
terms and conditions
apply for delays if you’ve booked using Snap.​

accordionContents.title: Can I bring my bike if I book with Eurostar Snap?

children.text: We’re sorry, you can’t bring a bike with you if you book a Snap ticket.

accordionContents.title: Can I add extra luggage to a Eurostar Snap booking?

children.text: Unfortunately, not. But our usual, generous, luggage policy still applies. You can bring two pieces of luggage and one piece of hand luggage.
See our full luggage policy
Seat selection is not available on Snap for now. If you're travelling as a group, we can't guarantee you'll be seated together​.

accordionContents.title: What are the benefits of Snap for Club Eurostar members?

children.text: You’ll be given the option to sign into your Club Eurostar account when making a booking with Eurostar Snap, so you can earn points and bonus points and you'll still have access to our Eurostar Lounges and priority ticket gates if your club tier allows. You can also spend points on Snap bookings.

However, the usual flexible travel perks for Avantage, Carte Blanche and Étoile members will not apply to Eurostar Snap bookings – Snap passengers can't travel on any Eurostar train to their destination on the day of their booking nor hop on the Eurostar train before or after the one booked, for free. The Club Eurostar class upgrade benefit also can’t be used in conjunction with Snap tickets.

accordionContents.title: Can I book a last-minute Snap ticket for a child?

children.text: Sadly not. Because we can’t guarantee that everyone in your party will be sat together, last-minute tickets are for passengers aged 16+ only. Infants under 4 years old can travel for free
on an adult's lap
. A maximum of one infant per adult can travel.

accordionContents.title: Can I use a discount code or an e-voucher when booking a Snap ticket?

children.text: You can't use a discount code when booking with Snap. But you can use an e-voucher.

accordionContents.title: Can I book a wheelchair space, a space for my guide/assistance dog or a companion ticket using Snap?

children.text: You can't book a wheelchair ticket. This is because the fares for wheelchair users available on eurostar.com are cheaper than Snap tickets.

But you can book a space for your/guide/assistance animal or a companion ticket. Just book your ticket using Snap as usual and then call our contact centre to book a companion ticket or a space for your guide/assistance animal. We request you pre-book
at least 24 hours before the departure date and time.

accordionContents.title: Can I book a companion ticket if I have reduced mobility or bring a guide/assistance animal?

children.text: Yes, you can. Book your ticket using Snap as usual and then call our contact centre to book a companion ticket or a space for your guide/assistance animal.
We request you pre-book
at least 24 hours before the departure date and time.
